#pre-requisites: security group ports open to YOU: SSH 22
#pre-requisites: Server is running Ubuntu or some Linux varient
#pre-requisites: Elastic IP address assigned
#pre-requisites: You have the SSH key to the server on your computer

#connecting to the server should be possible with:

ssh -i "(server-key.pem)" ubuntu@(elastic-ip-address-of-server)


#On a computer you will want to run these commands to connect to the Server

ssh-add (server-key.pem)

nautilus sftp://ubuntu@(elastic-ip-address-of-server)

# Within the file browser nautilus, you'll now be able to interact with the file system
